trend_summary: Satellite series shows steady infill and commercial expansion. Detached housing fabric remains, but tree cover slowly thins. The rail-corridor east gains large warehouses, residential buildings, parking decks and a stadium-sized facility, while new roads and small retail pads appear along main arteries. Overall footprint grows moderately; densification is localised, keeping a leafy, low-rise suburban character.
notable_changes: Large warehouse/parking complex built along the eastern rail corridor, replacing open ground.
Stadium-scale oval structure and adjacent lots added mid-period.
Progressive infill housing on vacant residential parcels in central blocks.
Tree canopy in western hills reduced by scattered clearing and new driveways.
Minor road realignments and new roundabouts improving access to commercial zone.
